Chelsea May Sell Malouda, Boost Bid for Porto’s Pereira: Soccer Roundup

-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 
2011-08-25T09:26:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/chelsea-may-sell-malouda-boost-bid-for-porto-s-pereira-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Chelsea May Raise Bid  Chelsea may improve its bid for Porto wing-back  Alvaro
Pereira  after an opening offer of 20 million euros ($29 million)
was rejected, the  Guardian  reported.  The  London  club is considering selling 31-year-old Florent Malouda to Italian side Juventus for a “knockdown fee,” the
paper said.  Barton to QPR?  Queens Park Rangers made Newcastle United player Joey Barton a three-year offer worth 9 million pounds ($15 million),
the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The midfielder, who is making 60,000 pounds a week at
Newcastle, will be out of contract next June.  Newcastle Chasing Inter Star  Newcastle wants to sign Inter Milan full-back Davide
Santon, the  Daily Mirror  reported. Liverpool, Manchester City
and Arsenal have also been tracking the 20-year-old Italy
international.  Arsenal Kaka Bid Rejected  An attempt by Arsenal to land Real  Madrid ’s Kaka on a one-
season loan has been rejected by the Spanish club, the  Daily
Mail  said.  Real Madrid wants 17.5 million pounds for the Brazilian
former World Player of the Year. Paris Saint-Germain and Sao
Paulo are also interested in the 29-year-old.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Danielle Rossingh in London at 
 drossingh@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 